    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"> </p>\n<div style=\"mso-element:para-border-div;border:none;border-bottom:solid windowtext 1.0pt;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext .75pt;padding:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in\">\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"border:none;mso-border-bottom-alt:solid windowtext .75pt;padding:0in;mso-padding-alt:0in 0in 1.0pt 0in\"><strong><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\">Trigger</span></strong><span style=\"mso-bidi-font-size:12.0pt;mso-bidi-font-family:Calibri;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-latin\"> You have temporary hit points and you or an ally within 30 feet would take damage.</span></p>\n</div>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"></p>\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\">You and the spirits that you are tied to have an empathic bond, driven by a shared suffering or contempt to protect against or to strike at your attackers. You can divert your temporary hit points to a target ally within range, allowing them to benefit from it as they take damage. Any remaining temporary hit points are then lost. If you are in Earthen Rage, you can then retaliate and deal mental or a type of elemental damage based on your elemental affinity equal to your level plus any remaining temporary hit points to a foe within five feet of your target. If you deal damage from your elemental affinity, this action loses its Emotion trait and gains that element’s trait.</p>"
